The true statements about paginated reports are:  A and D.

A. They are formatted to fit well on a page.
D. They are both printable and shareable.

So the correct options are A and D.

A. They are formatted to fit well on a page.
Reason.
Paginated reports are designed and formatted to fit well on printed pages or digital display, ensuring they look good when viewed or printed.
D. They are both printable and shareable.
Reason.
Paginated reports are designed to be both printable and shareable, making it easy to distribute information in a structured format.
